  "text": "Cell culture. Human T-lymphoblastic leukemia cell line CCRF-CEM (15) and its MTX-resistant RFC-deficient subline R2 (20) were cultured as described [CITATION_1] and were negative for Mycoplasma contamination (Mycoplasma Plus PCR primers, Stratagene, La Jolla, CA). For 200-to 1,000-mL cultures, cells were expanded in T-75 flasks (60-mL medium) incubated on their sides at 37j and 5% CO 2 . Logarithmically growing (3 Â 10 5 -5 Â 10 5 /mL) cells were inoculated into spinner flasks at z7 Â 10 4 cells/mL. The spinner flask headspace was sparged for 1 to 2 minutes with 5% CO 2 through a sterile plugged pipette. Flasks were sealed and stirred (60-120 rpm) at 37j. CCRF-CEM growth inhibition in continuous and intermittent drug exposures was measured as described [CITATION_2] . EC 50 values were determined from plots of percent control growth versus the logarithm of drug concentration.",
